Replaces the shared demo scene with a dedicated cell view built to the visual
standard of commercial cell software (RoboDK / Visual Components class),
driven entirely by real sim state:

- 4-axis palletizer arm (base yaw + shoulder + elbow + leveling wrist) with
  analytic 2-link IK; 2.10m reach verified numerically over the pick point
  and every pallet placement target (0 NaN poses, 0 reach clamps, 0.0000m FK
  error across 28 targets)
- The active carton is VISIBLY picked from the infeed conveyor, carried along
  a lift-traverse-lower path under the vacuum plate, and released on the
  pallet; queued cartons creep forward on the belt
- Andon stack light wired 1:1 to the edge state machine (green IDLE, blue
  MOVING, amber EXCEPTION_HANDLING, red FAULT_ESTOP) with pulsing emissive
- EXCEPTION/FAULT physically hold the arm pose — no interpolation while the
  VLM analyzes or the E-stop is latched
- VLM camera over the pick station; view cone flares amber while analyzing
- Suction pads tint green->amber->red with real gripper wear
- Safety fencing, hazard floor striping, fog, shadows, camera presets
  (OVERVIEW / GRIPPER / PALLET)

Build clean; demos route 22.3kB (scene code splits into the shared three.js
chunk)
